More than 500 people arrested during lastweek's riots in northern Nigeria will face summary trial by ajudicial tribunal, President Ibrahim Babangida said.    He said investigations showed the the violence wascarefully planned by "evil men" and those arrested would be triedfor arson, murder, rape and treason, some of which carry thedeath penalty.    Babangida said the crisis was "the civilian equivalent of anattempted coup d'etat" against the government. Reuter&#3;